Our world is not designed to help us stop and reflect on the presence of God at any given moment.
The Holy Spirit was present from the very beginning and even to the very end of the age (Matt.
The Holy Spirit has many other names in Scripture, including advocate, counselor, breath, wind, life, and Spirit of Truth.
Just as Jesus is described as a friend to believers, the Holy Spirit can be described as a helpful guide.
But the Holy Spirit will never let us run so far that we are no longer in his presence.